Mary Emma Wyckoff, respondent, v. Seth W. Scofield, et al., appellants. Decided December 1, 1884. Appeal from order directing the payment to receiver of certain rents collected. Harrison & Langdon, for appellant. W. I. Butler, for respondent. S. A. Noyes, for receiver.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Van Vorst and Freedman, JJ

Per Curiam.

The order should be affirmed, with costs, on the opinion rendered by the learned judge at special term.
